ecause they lack the necessary training.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Timely intervention</strong> - Bystander CPR can double the survival rate, but only 32% of out-of-hospital cardiac arrest victims receive CPR from a bystander.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-brPMkR cnEYUf pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Debunking common myths about BLS training</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-61_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-62_ pf-text-1"><strong>"I've been trained once; I donâ€™t need a refresher."</strong></li></ul><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-64_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-65_ pf-text-1">Reality: BLS skills can deteriorate over time. The Resuscitation Council UK recommends refresher training at least annually to maintain proficiency.</li></ul><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-67_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-dNsUpz eAuVCY pf-68_ pf-text-1"><strong>"BLS is only for healthcare professionals."</strong></li></ul><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-EROOM foKNLL pf-70_">